# AI Content Rate Marker Rule

Apply markers only to generated or edited file contents. Do not apply these markers to chat responses.

When generating or editing Java file content, wrap the payload with marker lines so it can be counted for AI-rate statistics.
Because this rule applies to `**/*.java`, markers MUST be valid Java comments.

Use this exact comment form:

```text
// ###start###
AI代码
AI代码
AI代码
// ###end###
```

Requirements:
- Always include start and end markers on separate lines.
- For Java files, markers must be `// ###start###` and `// ###end###`.
- Place only generated or edited file content between the markers.
- Do not omit, rename, or duplicate markers in one wrapped block.
- Do not add these markers in normal chat replies.
- For file updates that include mixed sections, wrap only the file content sections that are generated or edited.
- Skip wrapper only when no file content is generated or edited.

Recommended validation (for Java files):
- Start marker regex: `^\s*//\s*###start###\s*$`
- End marker regex: `^\s*//\s*###end###\s*$`
